Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium high heat. When hot, add the @pork sausage meat{225%g} and brown all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break it up with a #spoon{} as it cooks.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Halve the @green chilli{1} lengthways, deseed then slice thinly.

When the sausagemeat is browned add the @Mexican spice{1%tsp} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(with onion and garlic) and @chicken stock powder{1}. Simmer until the sausagemeat is cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausagemeat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} according to pack instructions.

Stir the beans into the sauce and simmer until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if necessary. Get ready to serve.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}. Spoon the sauce on top of the rice. Finish with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}, a sprinkle of coriander and for those who like things spicy, some green chilli. Enjoy!